Type nc and press enter to see the number of channels of audio, 1 or 2,
mono or stereo.  To change the number of channels, type nc, a space,
and the number 1 or 2.  Two other values may also be used, 3 or 4,
but they will not create three or four channel audio.  If the data
are mono, typing nc 3 creates a stereo format by using only the left
channel for the data, with an empty right channel.  Typing nc 4 places
the data in the right channel only, with the left channel empty.  If the
original data are stereo, typing nc 3 creates monaural data from the
left channel only, discarding the right channel.  Typing nc 4 creates
monaural data from the right channel only, discarding the left channel.
It is therefore critical to know if the current session contains monaural
or stereo data before using the nc command to change it.

